HEADWORD: Ruberythrinic
<hw>Ru`ber*y*thrin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ruber</ets> red + <ets>erythrin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid extracted from madder root.
It is a yellow crystalline substance from which alizarin is
obtained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rubescence</ent>⟦br⟧
